Package: krill-mcp
Version: 0.0.5
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: openjdk-21-jre-headless | openjdk-21-jre | openjdk-25-jre-headless | openjdk-25-jre, openssl
Maintainer: Benjamin Sautner <ben@krill.zone>
Description: Krill Model Context Protocol (MCP) server
 Exposes a Krill swarm to Claude Desktop and Claude Code as a remote MCP
 server. Install once on any Debian host on your LAN — the Claude client
 connects as a Custom Connector and can query every Krill server listed
 in /etc/krill-mcp/config.json using the same 4-digit cluster PIN.
 .
 Authentication uses Krill's PIN-derived Bearer token. When installed
 alongside the krill server package, /etc/krill-mcp/credentials/pin_derived_key
 is symlinked to the existing /etc/krill/credentials/pin_derived_key, so
 no re-entry of the PIN is required.
 .
 Listens on port 50052 by default. Learn more at https://krillswarm.com
